By Martins Ifijeh Nigeria has recorded 195 new cases of COVID-19, bringing to 57,437 the number of confirmed cases in the country. Announcing this yesterday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) said Enugu recorded 51 new cases; Gombe, 40; Lagos, 39; Plateau, 23; Federal Capital Territory (FCT), 15; Rivers, 12; Kaduna, eight; Ondo, three; Bauchi, two; while Edo and Ogun recorded one each. It said: “Nigeria has so far recorded 57,437 cases of COVID-19. 48,674 patients have been discharged, while 1,100 persons have died.”